        "text": "*[Bug 19094] New: `fillStrokeGrob()` bug with `x = textGrob()` and `col = NA` arguments in Cairo devices*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19094>\n\n            Bug ID: 19094\n           Summary: `fillStrokeGrob()` bug with `x = textGrob()` and `col\n                    = NA` arguments in Cairo devices\n           Product: R\n           Version: R-devel (trunk)\n          Hardware: Other\n                OS: All\n            Status: UNCONFIRMED\n          Severity: normal\n          Priority: P5\n         Component: Graphics\n          Assignee: <mailto:R-core@R-project.org|R-core@R-project.org>\n          Reporter: <mailto:trevor.l.davis@gmail.com|trevor.l.davis@gmail.com>\n\nCreated attachment 3743\n  --&gt; <https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/attachment.cgi?id=3743&amp;action=edit>\nFix `fillStrokeGrob()` bug in Cairo graphics devices for `textGrob()` argument\nand transparent `col`\n\nCurrently `fillStrokeGrob()` (as well as `fillGrob()`) fails to render in Cairo\ngraphics devices if it's `x` argument is a `textGrob()` and it's `gp` argument\nincludes `col = NA`.\n\n```\nlibrary(grid)\n# Expected: brown-filled text, no stroke\n# Actual on cairo (before fix): blank\npng(\"fill_text_col_na.png\", type = \"cairo\")\ngrid.newpage()\ntg &lt;- textGrob(\"RSTATS\", gp = gpar(fontsize = 72))\ngrid.draw(fillStrokeGrob(tg, gp = gpar(fill = \"brown\", col = NA)))\ndev.off()\n```",
